LAMMPS (23 Jun 2022 - Update 1)
# Argon simulation: NPT Equilibration followed by NVE Production
units           metal
atom_style      atomic
dimension       3
boundary        p p p

# Define simulation box
lattice         fcc 4.05
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.05 4.05 4.05
region          box block 0 4 0 4 0 4
create_box      1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.2 16.2 16.2)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms    1 box
Created 256 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.2 16.2 16.2)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds

# Define Lennard-Jones interactions for Argon
pair_style      lj/cut 10.0
pair_coeff      1 1 0.0103 3.4 10.0  # (ε = 0.0103 eV, σ = 3.4 Å, cutoff = 10 Å)

# Set atomic mass
mass            1 39.948

# Set initial velocities at 80 K (liquid phase for Argon)
velocity        all create 80 10 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian

# ----- NPT EQUILIBRATION -----
fix             1 all npt temp 80 80 0.1 iso 1.0 1.0 1.0
timestep        0.001  # 1 fs
thermo          1000
run             100000  # 100 ps
Generated 0 of 0 mixed pair_coeff terms from geometric mixing rule
